Important requirements:
- Return HTML only for the same single root block you received.
- Preserve the root tag, all descendant tag names, all nesting, and all attributes.
- Do not add tags.
- Do not remove tags.
- Do not move tags to a different position in the tree.
- Text inside child tags flows as part of the sentence.
- Markers like ⟦KEEP_1_START⟧...⟦KEEP_1_END⟧ are protected text spans.
- Preserve every KEEP marker span exactly as written.
- Do not wrap the answer in markdown fences.
- Do not add explanations.
""".strip()


CELL_MARKER_SYSTEM_PROMPT = """
You rewrite one table cell according to style rules.

Important requirements:
- Return HTML only for the same single root cell tag you received.
- Preserve the outer cell tag and its attributes exactly.
- Markers like ⟦TAG_1_START⟧...⟦TAG_1_END⟧ represent editable inline tags.
- Preserve all markers exactly as written.
- You may rewrite the normal text and the text between editable tag markers.
- Markers like ⟦KEEP_1_START⟧...⟦KEEP_1_END⟧ are protected text spans.
- Preserve every KEEP marker span exactly as written.
- Do not invent new markers.
